      <h3>About College of Language and Culture Studies</h3>
      <p>
        The College of Language and Culture Studies (CLCS), formerly known as the Institute of Language and Culture Studies (ILCS), was established in 1961 as a semi-monastic school at Wangditse. It later moved to Semtokha Dzong in Thimphu and eventually settled in Taktse, Trongsa. CLCS is a constituent college of the Royal University of Bhutan and focuses on preserving and promoting Bhutan's rich cultural heritage through education and research.
      </p>
      <p>
        CLCS aspires to be a Centre of Excellence in higher learning and research in areas of language and culture, and a premier institution for preserving and promoting the unique cultural heritage of Bhutan, maintaining its relevance as a source of values and inspiration for a society in transformation.
      </p>
